Description: Terracaptus is an online auction marketplace that allows to buy and sell intellectual property.
Full Description: TerraCaptus is the first on-line patent auction website of its kind, providing a venue in which patents can be easily listed and auctioned in an innovative and intuitive on-line system - and without any fees or costs until the patent is sold. In TerraCaptus' on-line patent auctions, the costs of setting up and conducting each auction are borne by TerraCaptus, and other costs normally associated with in-person patent auctions (e.g., for travel, lodging, and other logistical issues) are eliminated. In this manner, TerraCaptus' web-based auction platform has the ability to increase the number of potential bidders for any given patent. The TerraCaptus patent auction model also eliminates traditional up-front patent auction costs, such as costs associated with identification of and communication with potential buyers, advertisement of the patent for sale, preparation of the auction, and conducting of the auction. TerraCaptus charges nothing for these services, and instead is compensated from the proceeds of sale of the patent. Also, TerraCaptus is only compensated from auctions that result in a sold patent, and receives compensation only when the patent seller receives payment for the patent sold. Using TerraCaptus, potential buyers of each patent listed for sale are identified by TerraCaptus using proprietary software and (optionally) recommendations from the patent owner. These potential buyers are contacted by TerraCaptus, and are invited to a scheduled auction hosted on TerraCaptus' website. Each TerraCaptus on-line auction is public, utilizes a unique interface on TerraCaptus' website to easily enable registered parties to bid, and is open for viewing by parties who have not registered to bid. The pioneering TerraCaptus on-line patent auction system promises to revolutionize the way patent buyers and sellers perform their transactions, bringing a new level of liquidity to this valuable class of assets.

Description: East and Associates is specialize in the environmental consulting business for the commercial real estate industry.
Full Description: We specialize in the environmental consulting business for the commercial real estate industry. Nearing our twenty-first year of business, our independent consulting services and project management expertise cover a broad range of the environmental spectrum.  The key to the successful completion of a real estate transaction is to know the potential risk of exposure to any liabilities and to incorporate those risks in the evaluation.  The most logical approach to handling these environmental hazards is to become informed about the problems so they can be appropriately managed.  It is our goal to meet every customer's need for environmental consulting or project management services in a prompt and professional manner. Our company has furnished hundreds of environmental assessment reports to financial institutions, real estate developers, investors and individuals.  The environmental site assessment reports are always completed in a timely manner.  Once our clients understand the environmental issues and the potential ramifications, we outline various courses of action with our goal toward minimizing costs and lessening current or potential liabilities. Throughout the years, we have formed strategic alliances with environmental consulting, contracting and service companies.  These alliances allow us to offer a broad range of environmental services.  Some of these services we furnish through our alliances include Phase II subsurface investigations, Phase III remediation services, VCP and IOP applications and consulting, groundwater monitoring, wetlands determination, endangered species review, asbestos, lead-based paint and mold inspection and management services and indoor air quality monitoring.

Description: Teledyne Cougar is designs and manufactures RF and microwave cascadable amplifiers and integrated assemblies.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Founded in 1986, Teledyne Cougar's extensive product line includes over 700 models, meeting the needs of over 400 active customers. Cougar is based in Sunnyvale, California - the heart of the Silicon Valley. Cougar's three facilities, two in Sunnyvale and one in Lakewood Colorado, total nearly 50,000 square-feet. Cougar's newest Sunnyvale facility houses the headquarters team and sales and design engineering activities. We've equipped the newest Sunnyvale facility with a fully self-contained engineering lab where engineers can oversee production of products from assembly through test characterization, all in a clean and certified environment. Manufacturing and additional engineering activities continue in the original Sunnyvale and Lakewood facilities. Teledyne Cougar recently acquired the assets of Avnet MTS, merging key MTS people, equipment and products into our business. MTS brings more than three decades of product and service experience from organizations such as Avantek and Pennstock. Cougar is not only committed to maintaining these products and services but we're excited to present them under the Teledyne Cougar banner for the first time and to nurture and grow them for years to come. Over the years, Cougar's key-to-growth has been consistent new product development and exemplary quality and service. Cougar's designs cover 100 kHz to 20 GHz and include amplifiers, VCO's, mixers, IQ products, switches, limiters, attenuators and multi-component integrated assemblies. We continually provide the highest quality and reliability in technically demanding applications for leading-edge customers including Raytheon, Boeing, Lockheed Martin, BAE Systems, General Dynamics, Northrop Grumman, NGST, Teradyne, Rockwell Collins, Saab, Astrium, and Alcatel. While Cougar maintains a strong presence in the space and military markets, we also deliver solutions for commercial applications and provide value-add manufacturing, testing, screening and packing services for all markets. In continuing our commitment to the highest quality standards, we undertook the daunting effort of double certification to two industry quality standards. In July 1998, Cougar successfully achieved certification to both MIL-PRF-38534 and ISO 9001-2000. The MIL-PRF-38534 certification is especially important to our continued pursuit of space business because Cougar received certification to both Classes H and K screening levels under the stringent TRB Option. Cougar is also certified to AS9100, satisfying our commitment to the aerospace community. Cougar's quality policy is a testament to these high standards: Quality-Performance-On Time. Cougar's daily success depends on the skills and experience of our staff. Bringing to Cougar varied corporate, educational, and training backgrounds, our staff's knowledge, skills and experience make Cougar the premier component and integrated assembly supplier in the RF and Microwave industry. Cougar's continual emphasis on the development and improvement of suppliers, processes, and products mean performance, reliability, and schedule advantages for our customers. We're familiar with the challenges our customers face, whether it's a state-of-the-art radar system, a multi-use communication satellite, or a back-end semiconductor ATE station. Our experience, product breadth, and exemplary staff are prepared for the challenge.

Description: Identity Hawk markets computersecurity software designed to protect users' identity, social security numbers and online profiles.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Using the data you enter in your identity profile, IdentityHawk calculates your Identity Health Score by analyzing the amount and types of your personal information that we detect across the Internet. You can get your identity theft risk calculated and take an action depending on the result.  As the part of the service IdentityHawk offers three kinds of identity security monitoring:     * Identity Monitoring. The software comb the Internet for "events" where your personal identifying information (e.g., names, current and previous addresses and phone numbers, your Social Security number) is being used.     * Breach Alert Monitoring. When a company or organization reports lost or stolen personal data, IdentityHawk will help you determine whether you're at risk.     * Cyber Monitoring. IdentityHawk monitoring service scours the deepest corners of the Internet to search for your personal information in "black market" chat rooms and other clandestine sites where identity thieves sell their stolen data.    * Identity Theft Insurance. If you become a victim of identity theft or fraud, you're eligible for up to $1 million in coverage for out-of-pocket expenses.
